    "eyebrow": "Orientation",
    "num": "01",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">01</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Orientation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Welcome to Introduction to the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Explore who the Texicans were and their cultural background</li><li>Understand the origins and meaning of the term 'Texican'</li><li>Set the stage for deeper study of early Texas history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This lesson begins by defining 'Texican' and exploring its etymology to establish a foundation for understanding this unique cultural group in Texas history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Consider how the term 'Texican' combines 'Tex' from Texas and '-ican' suggesting identity, reflecting a blend of cultural influences.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on what you already know about Texas history and what questions you have about the Texicans.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid assuming 'Texican' simply means 'Texan' without recognizing its specific historical and cultural context.</p></div></div>",
