    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concept</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Cultural and Linguistic Background of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans spoke Spanish and English, reflecting bilingual heritage</li><li>They practiced Catholicism influenced by Spanish colonial traditions</li><li>Family and community life centered on frontier ranching and farming</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texicans' cultural identity was shaped by language, religion, and lifestyle rooted in Spanish and Mexican traditions adapted to frontier conditions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican family might celebrate Catholic holidays while engaging in cattle ranching typical of frontier life.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify how language and religion contribute to cultural identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid assuming cultural practices were uniform; frontier life required adaptation and blending.</p></div></div>",
