    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concept</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Settlement Patterns of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans settled primarily in South and Central Texas along rivers and fertile land</li><li>Communities were often isolated frontier ranches and small villages</li><li>Settlement patterns reflected adaptation to environmental and political conditions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlements were shaped by geography and the need for self-sufficiency in a frontier environment, influencing social and economic life. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Settlements near the Rio Grande allowed Texicans to engage in trade and ranching while maintaining cultural ties.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Map where you think Texican communities might have formed based on environmental factors.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid assuming Texican settlements were urban or densely populated; many were rural and dispersed.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best describes the cultural background of the Texicans?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;They were primarily Anglo settlers with no Mexican influence.&quot;,&quot;They had Spanish colonial roots and Mexican identity blended with frontier experiences.&quot;,&quot;They were Native Americans living in Texas before colonization.&quot;,&quot;They were recent immigrants from Europe with no ties to Mexico.&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The Texicans&#39; cultural background is a blend of Spanish colonial heritage, Mexican identity, and frontier family experiences, as covered in the course.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the role of the Texicans in early Texas history, including their political loyalties and participation in conflicts.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A complete answer should mention the Texicans&#39; complex loyalties, their participation in conflicts such as the Texas Revolution, and their position between Spanish, Mexican, and Anglo interests.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texicans were early settlers of Spanish and Mexican descent who played a significant role in early Texas history. They had complex political loyalties, often supporting Mexico but sometimes conflicted during the Texas Revolution. They participated in military and political events that shaped Texas&#39;s path to independence.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans had Spanish-Mexican roots and were involved in early Texas conflicts with divided loyalties.&quot;,&quot;They supported Mexico but had nuanced roles during the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were culturally Mexican settlers who participated in political and military events in early Texas.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
