    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">10</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concept</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Lifestyle and Economy of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Economy centered on cattle ranching, farming, and trade</li><li>Social life revolved around family, church, and community events</li><li>Texicans adapted Mexican customs to frontier realities</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican life combined economic activities suited to the frontier with cultural traditions inherited from Mexican and Spanish roots. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Ranching was both an economic necessity and a cultural practice, with rodeos and fiestas reflecting social life.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how economic activities might influence cultural traditions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid viewing frontier life as solely economic; social and cultural practices were deeply intertwined.</p></div></div>",
