    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Practices</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Language, Religion, and Traditions of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Spanish was the primary language spoken by Texicans</li><li>Catholic religious practices shaped festivals and daily life</li><li>Texicans preserved Spanish and Mexican culinary and musical traditions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was expressed through language, religion, and traditions that reflected their Spanish and Mexican heritage. These cultural practices distinguished them from Anglo settlers and reinforced community identity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Celebrations such as patron saint festivals combined religious observance with social gatherings featuring traditional music and food.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify cultural practices that helped maintain Texican identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the role of cultural practices in sustaining community cohesion.</p></div></div>",
