    "eyebrow": "Cultural Complexity",
    "num": "17",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">17</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Complexity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Hybrid Identity: Spanish, Mexican, and Frontier Influences</h2><ul><li>Texican identity blended Spanish colonial, Mexican national, and frontier elements</li><li>Cultural hybridity created unique social norms and practices</li><li>This complexity challenges simple ethnic or national labels</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture cannot be reduced to a single origin; it is a hybrid shaped by layered historical influences and frontier realities. This complexity requires nuanced understanding beyond binary categories. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican legal customs combined Spanish land grant traditions with adaptations to frontier governance.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss examples of cultural hybridity in Texican society.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Simplifying Texican identity as either purely Mexican or Anglo.</p></div></div>",
