    "id": "slide28",
    "eyebrow": "Frontier Lifestyle",
    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Frontier Lifestyle</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Daily Life and Economy of Texican Settlers</h2><ul><li>Texicans practiced subsistence farming and ranching</li><li>Communities were tight-knit with shared labor and defense</li><li>Frontier life required adaptability to environmental and social challenges</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlers lived a frontier lifestyle centered on farming, livestock, and mutual support. Their economy was largely self-sufficient, with community cooperation essential for survival amid environmental hardships and occasional conflicts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Ranching cattle was a key economic activity, with families working together to manage herds and protect them from raids.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how community cooperation helped Texicans manage frontier challenges.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing frontier life as isolated rather than socially interconnected and cooperative.</p></div></div>",
