    "num": "29",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">29</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Environmental Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Natural Hazards and Their Impact on Texican Settlements</h2><ul><li>Droughts and floods periodically threatened crops and homes</li><li>Wildlife and disease posed ongoing risks</li><li>Settlers developed adaptive strategies to mitigate environmental threats</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlers faced frequent natural hazards that could devastate crops, livestock, and infrastructure. Their survival depended on developing strategies such as crop diversification, water management, and community support systems. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> During drought periods, Texicans shifted to drought-tolerant crops and rationed water resources collectively.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify environmental hazards and propose adaptive responses Texicans might have used.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the severity and frequency of environmental hazards on frontier life.</p></div></div>",
