    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Mapping Activity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mapping Texican Settlements and Environmental Features</h2><ul><li>Use historical maps to locate key Texican settlements</li><li>Identify rivers, plains, and other geographic features influencing settlement</li><li>Analyze spatial relationships between settlements and environment</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mapping exercises help visualize how Texican settlements aligned with environmental features, revealing patterns of resource use and strategic location choices. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Plotting San Antonio and surrounding settlements along the San Antonio River illustrates clustering near water sources.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Create a map marking Texican settlements and major geographic features; discuss how environment influenced settlement choices.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the environmental context when interpreting settlement locations.</p></div></div>",
