    "eyebrow": "Group Discussion",
    "num": "31",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Group Discussion</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Challenges of Frontier Life for Texicans</h2><ul><li>Environmental hardships including drought and floods</li><li>Threats from conflicts with indigenous groups and other settlers</li><li>Economic uncertainty and isolation from larger markets</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans faced multifaceted challenges on the frontier that tested their resilience and community cohesion. Discussing these challenges deepens understanding of their lifestyle and survival strategies. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Frontier isolation meant limited access to goods and support, requiring self-sufficiency and strong local networks.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> In groups, discuss which challenges were most critical for Texican survival and how communities addressed them.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on environmental challenges without considering social and economic factors.</p></div></div>",
