    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Case Study</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">San Antonio: A Texican Settlement Example</h2><ul><li>Founded as a Spanish mission and presidio site</li><li>Evolved into a cultural and economic center for Texicans</li><li>Strategically located on the San Antonio River with fertile land</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">San Antonio exemplifies Texican settlement patterns, combining strategic geography, cultural heritage, and economic activity to sustain a frontier community. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The mission system in San Antonio provided religious, social, and economic infrastructure supporting Texican settlers.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how San Antonio’s location and history influenced its development as a Texican hub.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing San Antonio solely as a military outpost rather than a multifaceted community.</p></div></div>",
