    "id": "slide33",
    "eyebrow": "Practice Checkpoint",
    "num": "33",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">33</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Assessing Texican Settlement Understanding</h2><ul><li>Identify key environmental factors influencing Texican settlements</li><li>Explain how Spanish land grants affected settlement geography</li><li>Describe typical economic activities of Texican frontier communities</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This checkpoint assesses learners’ grasp of Texican settlement patterns, environmental context, and lifestyle, reinforcing key concepts before advancing. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A learner might explain that Texicans settled near rivers due to water access and fertile soil, supported by Spanish land grant policies encouraging cultivation.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief summary connecting environment, legal frameworks, and lifestyle in Texican settlements.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Separating environmental and legal influences instead of integrating them in explanations.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide33\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best describes the cultural background of the Texicans?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;They were primarily Anglo settlers with no Mexican influence.&quot;,&quot;They had Spanish colonial roots and Mexican identity blended with frontier experiences.&quot;,&quot;They were Native Americans living in Texas before colonization.&quot;,&quot;They were recent immigrants from Europe with no ties to Mexico.&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The Texicans&#39; cultural background is a blend of Spanish colonial heritage, Mexican identity, and frontier family experiences, as covered in the course.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the role of the Texicans in early Texas history, including their political loyalties and participation in conflicts.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A complete answer should mention the Texicans&#39; complex loyalties, their participation in conflicts such as the Texas Revolution, and their position between Spanish, Mexican, and Anglo interests.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texicans were early settlers of Spanish and Mexican descent who played a significant role in early Texas history. They had complex political loyalties, often supporting Mexico but sometimes conflicted during the Texas Revolution. They participated in military and political events that shaped Texas&#39;s path to independence.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans had Spanish-Mexican roots and were involved in early Texas conflicts with divided loyalties.&quot;,&quot;They supported Mexico but had nuanced roles during the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were culturally Mexican settlers who participated in political and military events in early Texas.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
