    "eyebrow": "Settlement Challenges",
    "num": "35",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">35</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Social and Political Pressures on Texican Communities</h2><ul><li>Pressure from Anglo-American settlers increasing in Texas</li><li>Conflicts with indigenous groups over land and resources</li><li>Navigating shifting political allegiances between Spain, Mexico, and settlers</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlements existed within a contested political and social frontier, requiring negotiation of complex relationships and loyalties amid external pressures. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texicans sometimes found themselves mediating between Mexican authorities and incoming Anglo settlers with differing interests.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how social and political pressures influenced Texican community cohesion and identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the political complexity and assuming Texicans had uniform loyalties or experiences.</p></div></div>",
