    "num": "38",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">38</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Military Roles</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans in Military Conflicts: Defenders and Fighters</h2><ul><li>Texicans participated in military actions defending Spanish and Mexican interests</li><li>They also fought alongside Anglo settlers during the Texas Revolution</li><li>Military involvement was tied to protecting land, family, and political ideals</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans played active military roles in early Texas conflicts, sometimes defending Spanish or Mexican authority and at other times joining Anglo settlers in rebellion. Their participation was motivated by local defense needs and political aspirations (s2, s8). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican militias fought in battles such as the Siege of Bexar, demonstrating their dual roles as defenders of Mexican rule and contributors to Texas independence efforts.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze why a Texican militia might choose to fight against Anglo settlers in one conflict but alongside them in another.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring Texicans' agency and treating them as passive bystanders in military history.</p></div></div>",
