    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">46</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Exercise</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyze a Timeline: Texican Political and Military Actions</h2><ul><li>Review a timeline of key events from 1821 to 1836</li><li>Identify moments of Texican allegiance shifts</li><li>Explain reasons for changes based on historical context</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This exercise helps learners apply timeline analysis to understand how Texican roles evolved during early Texas history (s2, s7, s8). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texicans supported Mexican rule after 1821 but increasingly joined Texas independence efforts by 1835.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Mark on the timeline where Texican loyalties shifted and write a brief explanation for each change.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to connect timeline events with broader political and social contexts.</p></div></div>",
