    "num": "47",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">47</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Common Misconceptions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Avoiding Oversimplification of Texican Roles</h2><ul><li>Texicans were not a monolithic group with uniform loyalties</li><li>Their political and military roles changed over time and context</li><li>Recognize the influence of local conditions and personal ties</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">A common mistake is to oversimplify Texican history by categorizing them strictly as Mexican loyalists or Texas separatists. Their roles were diverse and evolving (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Texicans fought at the Alamo defending Mexican rule, others later supported Texas independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on how oversimplification can distort understanding of historical groups.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring evidence of shifting loyalties and diverse motivations.</p></div></div>",
