    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">51</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Hands-On Activity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing a Texican Primary Source Document</h2><ul><li>Select a document from s10 or s11 collections</li><li>Identify key information: author, date, purpose</li><li>Note language indicating cultural or political views</li><li>Reflect on what the document reveals about Texican life</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This activity develops skills in extracting and interpreting historical information from authentic Texican sources. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land deed shows settlement patterns and legal claims, reflecting Texican adaptation to frontier life.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief summary of your document’s significance and any questions it raises.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on surface details without considering deeper implications or context.</p></div></div>",
