    "eyebrow": "Source Reliability",
    "num": "52",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">52</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Source Reliability</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Challenges in Interpreting Texican Primary Sources</h2><ul><li>Incomplete or damaged documents</li><li>Author bias and political agendas</li><li>Translation and transcription errors</li><li>Limited perspectives, often excluding indigenous or marginalized voices</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Recognizing these challenges is essential to responsibly use primary sources in reconstructing Texican history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A newspaper article (s15) may exaggerate events to sway public opinion during the Texas Revolution.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify potential reliability issues in a chosen Texican source and suggest ways to mitigate them.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring source limitations and overgeneralizing from a single document.</p></div></div>",
