    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">53</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interpreting Texican History Through Primary Sources</h2><ul><li>Primary sources provide direct insight but require critical reading</li><li>Understanding context and bias is key to accurate interpretation</li><li>Multiple sources enrich and complicate historical narratives</li><li>Learners develop skills to question and analyze evidence</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflecting on the process of primary source analysis helps consolidate critical thinking and historical understanding. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Comparing a Texican soldier’s letter with Mexican government records reveals contrasting views on loyalty.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on how primary sources changed or confirmed your understanding of the Texicans.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to integrate multiple perspectives or questioning assumptions.</p></div></div>",
