    "num": "55",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">55</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Field Disagreements</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Contested Points in Texican History</h2><ul><li>Debate over Texican political loyalties during the Texas Revolution</li><li>Disagreement on the extent of cultural assimilation vs. preservation</li><li>Varied interpretations of Texican settlement motivations</li><li>Challenges in defining Texican identity across time and space</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Scholars differ on key aspects of Texican history due to limited evidence and interpretive frameworks. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some historians emphasize Texican loyalty to Mexico, others highlight their push for independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify one contested point and argue for a position using evidence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming a single definitive narrative without acknowledging scholarly debate.</p></div></div>",
